BEGIN_TEXT

Find the Taylor series in \((x-a)\) through \((x-a)^{3}\) for
 
\[ f(x) = 2 - x + 3x^{2} - x^{3}, \quad a = -1 \]

$PAR

\( f(x) = \) \{ans_rule(5)\} \(+\)
             \{ans_rule(5)\} \((x+1)     + \)  
             \{ans_rule(5)\} \((x+1)^{2} + \)
             \{ans_rule(5)\} \((x+1)^{3}   \).

END_TEXT

$ans0 =   7;
$ans1 = -10;
$ans2 =   6;
$ans3 = - 1;

ANS(num_cmp($ans0));
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans3));

